<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Root Beer Pork
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 (4 pound) pork shoulder or butt
2 (12 oz.) cans of regular or diet root beer
1-2 (18 oz.) bottle(s) of barbecue sauce (I used 1 Â½ bottles)
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Place the pork roast in slow cooker.
Pour the root beer over the meat.
Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or until pork shreds easily with a fork.
After pork has cooked, drain and discard the root beer and any chunks of fat.
Shred the pork and place it back in the slow cooker.
Pour the barbecue sauce over the pork; stir to combine.
Let it warm on low for 10-15 minutes.
</instructions>
</recipe>
